knowledge_graph.title: Sourdough Bread
knowledge_graph.description: Sourdough or sourdough bread is a bread made by the fermentation of dough using wild lactobacillaceae and yeast. Lactic acid from fermentation imparts a sour taste and improves keeping qualities.

related_questions.question: Is sourdough better for you than bread?
related_questions.snippet: The bottom line Sourdough is a healthier alternative to regular white or whole wheat bread. Although it has comparable nutrients, the lower phytate levels mean it is more digestible and nutritious. The prebiotics also help to keep your gut bacteria happy, and it may be less likely to spike blood sugar levels.
related_questions.title: Why sourdough bread is healthier than regular white or wheat bread

related_questions.question: What is so special about sourdough bread?
related_questions.snippet: According to some studies, sourdough bread acts as a prebiotic, which means that the fiber in the bread helps feed the “good” bacteria in your intestines. These bacteria are important for maintaining a stable, healthy digestive system. Sourdough is also lower in gluten than other forms of bread.
related_questions.title: Sourdough Bread: Is It Good for You? - WebMD

related_questions.question: What is the difference between sourdough and normal bread?
related_questions.snippet: Sourdough bread is made through slow, natural fermentation. While other breads have added yeast to help the dough rise quickly, sourdough uses a 'starter' made of flour and water, which contains wild yeasts and bacteria.
related_questions.title: Is sourdough bread healthy? - British Heart Foundation

related_questions.question: What makes sourdough bread different?
related_questions.snippet: Sourdough is naturally leavened bread, which means it doesn't use commercial yeast to rise. Instead, it uses a 'starter' – a fermented flour and water mixture that contains wild yeast and good bacteria – to rise. This also produces the tangy flavour and slightly chewy texture you'll find in sourdough.
related_questions.title: What is sourdough? - BBC Good Food
